title: [SOLVED]820-3209-A Does not seem to charge, dim or no green light on charger
message:
Edit: Solved

When you plug in the charger, in OSX it thinks it is at 100%, but when you unplug it, it will go back to whatever it was before. There was liquid damage, U7100 was replaced and a wire was run from pin 18 to r7130 since the line was burnt, and the SMC was reflowed. I'm guessing this has something to do with sys_onewire?

title: [SOLVED]820-3209-A Does not seem to charge, dim or no green light on charger
message: Without a green light it will never charge. Check ACOK from U7100, but first suspect is also the IO board+cable.

title: [SOLVED]820-3209-A Does not seem to charge, dim or no green light on charger
message: Yup, looks like it was just the board & cable, the motherboard is just fine
